-Introduction
		-Javascript is a dynamic computer programming language. 
		-It is lightweight and most commonly used as a part of web pages, whose implementations allow client-side script to interact with the user and 	  make dynamic pages. 
		-It is an interpreted programming language with object-oriented capabilities.

-Client-side JavaScript
		-Client-side JavaScript is the most common form of the language. 
		-The script should be included in or referenced by an HTML document for the code to be interpreted by the browser.

-Advantages of JavaScript

		-Less server interaction
		-Immediate Feedback to the users
		-Increased Interactivity
		-Richer Interfaces

-Applications

		-Error Handling
		-Validation
		-Animation
		-Multimedia
		-Debugging etc.

-Top 5 Popular JavaScript Frameworks

		-Node.JS
		-Meteor.JS
		-React.JS
		-Ember.js
		-Angular 2

-JavaScript can be implemented using JavaScript statements that are placed within the 
	
	<script>... </script>

	Syntax:

	<script type="text/javascript">
   Your code here.
	</script>

	#1 Example

		<script type="text/javascript">
         
            document.write("Hello World!")
         
      </script>

-Loading external js
	
	<script type="text/javascript" src="">  

	</script>

-Features
	
		-Whitespace and Line Breaks

		-Case Sensitivity

		-Comments in JavaScript

			-JavaScript supports both C-style and C++-style comments
			-Any text between a // and the end of a line is treated as a comment and is ignored by JavaScript.
			-Any text between the characters /* and */ is treated as a comment

			#2 Example

			<script type="text/javascript">
 
   
			      // This is a comment. It is similar to comments in C++
			   
			      /*
			      * This is a multiline comment in JavaScript
			      * It is very similar to comments in C Programming
			      */
			   
			   	  //
			</script>


#3 Example 

		<!DOCTYPE html>
		<html>
		<head>
			<title></title>
		</head>
		<body>
		<script type="text/javascript">
			var a=10;
			var b=20;
			var sum= a + b;
			document.write(sum);

		</script>
		</body>
		</html>

#4 Example

<html>

   <head>
   
      <script type="text/javascript">
       
            function hello() 
            {
               alert("hello Everyone.");
            }
         
      </script>
      
   </head>
   
   <body>
      <input type="button" onclick="hello();" value="Hello" />
   </body>
   
</html>


#5 Example: External JS

<html>

   <head>
      <script type="text/javascript" src="filename.js" ></script>
   </head>
   
   <body>
    <input type="button" onclick="Hello();" value="Hello" />
    </body>
</html>

-Data types
	-Numbers: var x=16, var y=16.5; 
	-String: var y='this is fourth sem';
	-Boolean: var y=true;
	-Object: Objects use names to access its "members". In this example, person.name returns hari.
			var x=
			{
				name:"hari",address:"ktm"
			};

	# Example

	<script type="text/javascript">

	let y='this is life';
	var x={
		name:"hari",address:"ktm"
		};

		var z=4;
	console.log(typeof x,typeof y);

	console.log(z);


	var person = ["Hari", "Thapa", 46];



	console.log(typeof person);

</script>

-Variable Scope

#6 Example: External JS

<html>
   <body onload = checkscope();>
      <script type = "text/javascript">
       
            var myVar = "global"; // Declare a global variable

            function checkscope() 
            {
               var myVar = "local";  // Declare a local variable
               document.write(myVar);
            }
        
      </script>
   </body>
</html> 


-Operators

#7 Example: External JS

		-Arithmetic Operators: + ,-, /, %, ++, --

		-Comparison Operators: ==, !=, <, >, >=

		-Logical (or Relational) Operators: &&, ||, !

		-Assignment Operators: =, +=, *=, /=, %=

		-Conditional (or ternary) Operators:



		<script>

		function check(num)
		 {
		  return (num ? "5" : "10");
		}
		</script>					
		
		<body>
		<script>
			
				console.log(check(true));
				// expected output: "$2.00"

				console.log(check(false));
				// expected output: "$10.00"

				console.log(check(5));
				// expected output: "$2.00"

				</script>
	</body>

	-JS Array:

		-var array_name = [item1, item2, ...];
		-var person=[hari,34,kathmandu];
		-var person=new array('hari','34','kathmandu');

		OR

		var person = [];
		e.g.:var person=[hari,34,kathmandu];
		
